description: {"blocks":[{"key":"ekae4","text":"Sampling different areas of the diseased or healthy liver and storing the tissue in a variety of mediums to allow for an in-depth characterization of heterogeneity and the identification of unique cell populations through the employment of multiomic technologies, such as single-cell RNA-sequencing, single-nucleus RNA-sequencing, flow cytometry, and spatial transcriptomics.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

This procedure should be performed in accordance with all applicable safety procedures and using aseptic technique.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bquht","text":"Collect explanted tissue section in 30mL of HBSS 1x with Ca2+ and Mg2+ in a 50mL conical tube and keep on ice, ideally to process within 30 minutes of removal from patient or removal from the flushed donor organ in preservation solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":59,"length":2},{"style":"sup","offset":68,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"419ju","text":"For the purpose of spatial transcriptomics, OCT-embed for the viable freezing and storing for future slicing of tissue for spatial analyses. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":42}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4rme","text":"O.C.T. (Optimal Cutting Temperature) Compound (Fisher Health Care 4585)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cl9uu","text":"Additional approach: Tissue snap frozen in liquid nitrogen can be embedded in OCT after LN storage and then processed for spatial transcriptomics.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":20}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"nurd","text":"For the purpose of single-nucleus RNA-sequencing snap-freeze (dry) for the maintenance and storage of nuclei.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":49}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"foml0","text":"Tissue should remain on ice in HBSS 1X with Ca2+ and Mg2+ until ready to be sectioned.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":46,"length":2},{"style":"sup","offset":55,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ine1","text":"Transfer tissue to a petri dish placed on top of a flat ice pack to begin sectioning with sterile scalpels and sterile forceps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1lium","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"buqlv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dtva2","text":"Section tissue for OCT-embedding, it should be equal to or smaller than 1cm x 1cm x 0.3 cm (W x L x H).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7cs1c","text":"Remove excess liquid around the tissue (e.g. by using a dry petri-dish surface).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"61ess","text":"Cover the base of the mold with a flat layer of OCT and place the tissue on top (OCT blocks must be pre-labeled).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"53d3v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7n6ve","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2kk3p","text":"Add OCT around and on top of the tissue (the tissue must be completely submerged in OCT).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"qc2b","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b2ppg","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8tphv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":101,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"b4d61","text":"To ensure complete submersion in OCT,  avoid the presence of bubbles above or surrounding the tissue.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7v5jj","text":"Place the OCT blocks on top of a flat layer dry ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4jd44","text":"When the block looks completely white, wrap them with plastic microfilm and secure the plastic, make sure to re-label on top of the plastic microfilm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"buaj4","text":"Store the blocks in -80ºC Fridge until future usage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"96io8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"rb45","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"b0skj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"102DCB504F0911ED90980B4229AAB0A5","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"-80","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"55ddf","text":"Fill and label a 15mL conical tube with 10mL of 10% Formalin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":48,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dcab5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a42am","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9mdet","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"k1ou","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":77,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"chihn","text":"Ensure label contains sample ID, date, lab name, and solution (10% Formalin).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7m25a","text":"For the purpose of histology and immunohistochemistry, formalin-fixing and paraffin-embedding (FFPE) tissue allows for the long-term storage of tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":55}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1g249","text":"Fill a canister with 1L of liquid nitrogen.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ca3gj","text":"Ensure to keep the tissue in the petri dish on the ice pack while sectioning, aim for a size of 1cm x 1cm x 1cm (W x L x H).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7dsfn","text":"Section tissue for snap-freezing, it should be approximately 1cm x 1cm x 0.3 cm (W x L x H) in size.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f25ci","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f7toq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"amiec","text":"Once frozen, use forceps to remove them from the container, and place them a cardboard box in a liquid nitrogen storage tank until future usage.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bktsm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cdqge","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"746ti","text":"Place the tissue section in the tube, fully submerged in 10% Formalin and keep it in the fridge until you are ready to submit it for paraffin-embedding and sectioning for stains. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f8k2n","text":"To ensure long-term storage and maintenance of RNA quality, ensure that the FFPE blocks are placed in 4ºC fridge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":113}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"87peb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7nj65","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2qslt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"EE0D11C04F0811ED90980B4229AAB0A5","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aeuud","text":"Label 1.5ml or 2ml cryovials with study ID, date, lab name, and \"Snap-Frozen.\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3hjhi","text":"Remove as much excess liquid as possible by placing it on a dry petri dish surface, then transfer to cryovial, close it shut and drop it in the liquid nitrogen container.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eq9f9","text":"Caudate will be perfused and dissociated as described in Human Liver Caudate Lobe Dissociation for ScRNA-seqV.2","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":57,"length":54}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"356127C065E111EDB061DD2F0EBACAC7","url":"https://www.protocols.io/view/human-liver-caudate-lobe-dissociation-for-scrna-se-q26g77j1gwz1/v2"}}}}
